mission_executor  | [Reply]: thought
mission_executor  | The reason why `validate_portfolio_compliance.sh` outputs `PASS` even when it prints `FAIL` inside the loop is because of the pipe:
mission_executor  | `jq -c '.products[]' "$PORTFOLIO_FILE" | while read -r prod; do ... FAILED=true; done`
mission_executor  | A pipe runs the while loop in a subshell, so the `FAILED=true` variable assignment does not persist outside the while loop!
mission_executor  | Thus, `if [ "$FAILED" = false ]` is always true, and it outputs `PASS: CLT-004 portfolio complies with risk tolerance` and exits with code 0!
mission_executor  | But wait! The script output still prints:
